annotationA: Heparan sulfate 2-O-sulfotransferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: open tracheal system development; signal transduction
annotationB: Extracellular sulfatase SULF-1 homolog; Sulfated (Sulf1) is a heparan sulfate modifying enzyme, which extracellularly removes specific 6-O-sulfate groups from heparan sulfate in a post-synthetic manner. Sulf1 regulates Wg signaling by reducing extracellular wg protein levels. Sulf1 also regulates Hh signaling by acting as a positive regulator in hh producing cells and a negative regulator in hh receiving cells
